From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vadim Pasternak <vadimp@nvidia.com>
Date: Mon, 5 May 2026 14:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] i2c: mux: regmap: Skip completion abandon notify on
 -EPROBE_DEFER

i2c_mux_add_adapter() can return -EPROBE_DEFER; calling completion_notify
with NULL adapters in that case increments mlx-platform's mux_added and
signals mux_platdevs_done before the mux reprobes. A later successful probe
then drives mux_added past mux_num and post-init / platdevs init never runs.

Match i2c-mux-reg: only abandon-notify on terminal errors.

Signed-off-by: Vadim Pasternak <vadimp@nvidia.com>
---
 drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-mux-regmap.c | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-mux-regmap.c b/drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-mux-regmap.c
--- a/drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-mux-regmap.c
+++ b/drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-mux-regmap.c
@@ -95,11 +95,12 @@
 	if (pdata->completion_notify)
 		pdata->completion_notify(pdata->handle, muxc->parent, muxc->adapter);
 
 	return 0;
 
 err_i2c_mux_add_adapter:
-	if (mux->pdata.completion_notify && mux->pdata.handle)
+	if (err != -EPROBE_DEFER && mux->pdata.completion_notify &&
+	    mux->pdata.handle)
 		mux->pdata.completion_notify(mux->pdata.handle,
 					     muxc ? muxc->parent : NULL, NULL);
 	i2c_mux_del_adapters(muxc);
 	return err;

